Java Says

Suppose we have

class Animal {

    void sound() {

    }

}

Question.

Can every animal make the same sound?

Dog?

Woof

Cat?

Meow

Lion?

Roar

No.

So parent class cannot decide.

It only knows

Every Animal has sound.

But how?

Child will decide.

Java Solution
abstract class Animal {

    abstract void sound();

}

Question.

Why

abstract

?

Because

Animal doesn't know the implementation.

It leaves it to children.

