First Abstract Class
abstract class Animal{

    abstract void sound();

}

Read it.

Animal is abstract.

↓

sound() exists.

↓

No body.

↓

Child must complete it.
Dog
class Dog extends Animal{

    void sound(){

        System.out.println("Woof");

    }

}

Dog completed the missing work.

Main
public class Main{

    public static void main(String[] args){

        Dog d=new Dog();

        d.sound();

    }

}

Output

Woof
